	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>THE SHADOW FALLS:TWILIGHT CHAPTER 4</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage Express 2.0">
<title>Untitled Normal Page</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p><marquee>*(A Thesis of The Cruel Angel), Like an angel that has no sense of mercy..., Rise, young child, to the heavens like a legend... Cold winds, as blue as the sea.Tear open the door to your heart, I see... But unknowing you seem, just staring at me... Standing there smiling serenely. Desperate, for something to touch... A moment of kindness like that in a dream... Your innocent eyes, have yet no idea... Of the path your destiny will follow... But someday you'll become aware of... Everything that you've got behind you...Your wings are for seeking out a new... Future that only you can search for. The cruel angel's thesis bleeds through a portal like your pulsing blood. If you should betray the chapel of your memories, Cruel angel's thesis enters.....through the window of your soul So, child, stand tall and embrace the fire of the legend. Embracing the universe like a blazing star!</marquee></p>

<p><br>
------------------------------<br>
Chapter 4 Destiny's Call<br>
------------------------------<br>
<br>
Once again in short period of time, Leylia was woke up inside a
jail cell. Everything hurt and seemed foggy as the<br>
effects of the poisoned shurikens began to taper off. Her head
was still spinning as she mulled over the last few<br>
moments she remembered, Reyas being killed., dark elf trying to....Who
was touching her now? Without looking she<br>
lashed out at the source and clobbered someone.<br>
<br>
&quot;OW!! What in the Hell are you doing! Snap out of it Leylia!&quot;<br>
<br>
Seemed like she had heard that voice before. She sat up off the
rock slab and stared at the voice. He was so blurry,<br>
white on top, lightly tanned everywhere else.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who....Are you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;They must have really knocked you about with those
shurikens. Come on! Come on! Wake up Leylia!&quot; He snapped his<br>
fingers in front of her.<br>
<br>
I know that voice... <br>
<br>
Leylia opened her eyes wider and he came into focus. It was that
silver haired boy, who stopped her before. The one<br>
who kept her from totally destroying Felwithe.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know..you...I think....&quot; She began to pass out
again, but the boy grabbed her, brought her back up so the could
look eye<br>
to eye. &quot;Leylia. I'm not playing with you. WAKE UP!! We have
to get out of here!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Who..are you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm hurt Leylia...I really am.&quot; The boy let go of her
for a moment and began to fumble with her pants.<br>
&quot;HEY!! Stop that you..you.....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;O stop your whining. I'm not going to hurt you.&quot; He
fumbled for a bit more, then pulled out her pendant and held it
in front<br>
of her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now do you remember!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Leylia began to cry. &quot;Poor Reyas..I couldnt save him...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;NO! NO! NO! I'm Reyas!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Are not..he's dead...&quot; Leylia whispered as she slipped
back into unconsciousness.<br>
<br>
&quot;O for crying out loud!.....This is going to take a long
time&quot;<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;Così fare| your report Tenrou. What happened to Joithe?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Joithe let his hormones over take his senses. He was killed
by the elf spy, I brought in.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And why didn't you kill her out in the field instead of
wasting resources in the dungeon?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not like Joithe. She may be a disgusting creature
barely worth our noble seed, but she is a disgusting creature
with<br>
valuable knowledge.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;How so?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;From what I could tell of her clothing, she is one of
Antonious Bayle's scouts. She will have valuable information of<br>
various outposts and human encampments.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And would even a human such as Bayle, make such a stupid
mistake of giving a scout vital information?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;As you said, humans are stupid creatures. Besides we won't
know until I...&quot; Tenrou smiles evilly &quot;interrogate her.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well. But do not take too long. We have other missions
for you to accomplish.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;For the damnation of Innoruuk.&quot;<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;Leylia! ..let go..can't breath!...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; I'm sorry Reyas. I'm just so glad you're alive!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You didn't listen to a word a told you before did you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not really. I was thinking about how hungry I was.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;....&quot; Reyas gives her an exasperated look. &quot;I
told you before, As long as your pendant is unharmed. I can't die.
I might<br>
disappear for a while, but I'll be back.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; So what's with the new shape?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, seeing how my job is to keep you alive. I had too or
I would have strangled you if you called me puppy again.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah..poor puppy.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;..must...... resist..urge to kill.....&quot;<br>
-------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;Co'me è| the prisoner right now?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There was some noise in the prisoner's cell a few moments
ago. But it has quieted down. Must have been tossing and<br>
turning due to the poison you put on her.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright then. Open up!&quot;<br>
<br>
The guard turns and fumbles the dungeon lock open. Tenrou enters
and then he is heard shouting.<br>
<br>
&quot;AHH P'RCA!!!! The prisoner has escaped!&quot;<br>
---------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;So how are we going to get out of here?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well while, you have been sleeping. I found us a hole that
leads up into the city.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And this is a good thing?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, it's better then waiting on them to come take you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Good point.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Watch this.&quot; Flexing his muscles Reyas grabs hold of
the cell bars and begins to tug on them. In a moment they begin
to<br>
groan and then they snap. Making a hole for Leylia to get through.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am so big and strong!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know about big....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;.....That's mean...&quot; He exits the cell and kneels
down, beginning to move a rock. The rock noisily tumbles away.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well here it is. Get in.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I can't fit in there!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You're going to have too! Now get crawling!&quot;<br>
<br>
The sounds of someone talking filter down into the dungeon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Leylia hurry up!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm stuck!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Perfect!&quot;<br>
<br>
The sounds of keys jingling begin to trickle down. <br>
<br>
&quot;Come on! Come on! Move your fat fanny!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;WHAT!?! Ow! Stop kicking me there!&quot;</p>

<p>As she finally squeezes through the hole and up the tunnel,
Reyas vanishes in a flash of light just as the door opens.<br>
<br>
&quot;AHH P'RCA!!!! The prisoner has escaped!&quot;<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
*(Music Cue: Rage against The Machine &quot;F**K the Police&quot;)<br>
<br>
&quot;Frett'a in su! Ritrova'mento| her!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There she is! Inside the Maiden's Fancy!&quot;<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
A small grate begins to move. Then Reyas emerges out of the hole,
to be greeted by screams of several women and<br>
flying articles of clothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ooooo&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What's going on up there?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing! Hurry on up!&quot;<br>
Leylia scurries up the rest of the way and pulls herself out of
the hole. Taking notice of where they are.<br>
<br>
&quot;Of course you would find the tunnel that leads into the
bordello.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What can I say? I hung around with your father too long.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;STEL'LE VENO!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Look out!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shurikens rip through the walls of the Maiden's Fancy. Both of
them dive to the ground just in time for the shurikens to<br>
pass inches over them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's move!&quot; <br>
<br>
Leaping back to there feet, they begin to madly search for an
exit. Every now and then more shurikens tear through the<br>
infrastructure of the building. Coming to a window they leap out
and spring off the adjacent wall and up to the roof of the<br>
Maiden's Fancy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Up there kill them!&quot;<br>
<br>
Several shurikens whiz by slicing through Reyas's arm. He ignores
them and jumps to the next building. Leylia follows<br>
quickly, and they continue jumping from rooftop to rooftop
towards Nektulos Forest.<br>
<br>
Several rogues pursue, hurling shurikens all the while.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cad'uta | back! I'll handle this!&quot;<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Reyas and Leylia make it out of the city, surprisingly easy.
After clearing the city center they encountered no resistance.<br>
That changed quickly once they entered Nektulos forest. A
shuriken whisked by only a few inches in front of them and<br>
carved itself into a nearby tree.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where do you think you're going?&quot; someone calls out of
thedarkened forest.<br>
<br>
&quot;We intend to leave here. Now step aside!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't who you are boy, but I'll thank you to be civil.
BLOODY SLICE!&quot;<br>
<br>
A reddish wave leapt out of the darkness and cut through the
earth, Reyas barely manages to flip out of the way and into<br>
an outlying tree branch.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now tell me girl. Why did you attempt to spy in this
territory! Why did Bayle send someone so pathetically untrained
here!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Bayle!?! Bayle who?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Insolent girl! BlOODY SLICE!&quot;<br>
<br>
Another wave leapt out and collided with a mana barrier
surrounding Leylia. The impact hit her so hard that it catapulted<br>
her away, making her skid across the forest floor.<br>
<br>
/LEYLIA!/<br>
<br>
I'm ok. Just got the wind knocked out of me. Now I'm going to
crush him!<br>
<br>
/Leylia wait! Don't../<br>
<br>
Leylia sprung to her feet and charged towards the voice.
Concentrating with all her might, two mana blades formed in her<br>
hands. &quot;DEMON'S DANCE!&quot;<br>
<br>
Her blades cut through the air, seemingly hitting nothing, then
several trees began to fall and a form leapt over her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;POISON STARS!&quot; <br>
Leylia worked quickly, her blades easily deflecting the shurikens.
She then turned and shifted her wait into a defensive<br>
stance as the Dark elf several feet in front of her. His eyes
looked her over and he smiled. <br>
<br>
&quot;I'm impressed you're not bad for woman. But you're no match
for me. POISON STARS!&quot;<br>
<br>
The shurikens arced out and then streaked back toward the Dark
elf, when they collided with a barrier around Leylia. The<br>
Dark elf easily dodged them. she then struck out at him with
unnatural speed, her strikes seeking out toward the elf faster<br>
then could be seen. Amazingly, the elf easily dodged the attacks.<br>
<br>
&quot;How's that for a woman!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very pretty precious. But unfortunately it's going to take
more then knocking away my shurikens and cheap illusion to<br>
best me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I can deal with that! DEMON'S DANCE!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;BLOODY SLICE!&quot;<br>
<br>
The attacks were about to collide then the mysteriously diverted
off course.<br>
<br>
&quot;What the !?!&quot;<br>
&quot;What the !?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Reyas stood in between them, a barrier shimmering around him.<br>
<br>
&quot;WILL YOU TWO LOVEBIRDS PLEASE KNOCK IT OFF!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;LOVE..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;BIRDS!!!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;YEEESH! You two! You fight as if you where married or
something!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;WHY YOU!!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;REYAS!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;HUSH! Aren't either of you the least bit interested as to
why your abilities are so evenly matched. Or why both of you<br>
have something in common!?! Or why the fact that neither of you
belong here!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What are you talking about!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Use your head Leylia! Why do you think we had such an easy
time getting out of here. Or why you got captured, or why<br>
that other elf didn't rape you when he had the chance. &quot;
Pointing to the Dark Elf &quot;He ordered the other assassins
back,<br>
and he is the one that kept them from raping you. My guess is, he
is a spy just like he thinks you are. Stop me if I am<br>
wrong!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Dark elf sheathed his sword. &quot;He's right. I was sent
here by Antonious Bayle to spy on the Dark elf movements.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why would a Dark elf betray his own people to help humans?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That should be obvious Leylia. He's not entirely Dark Elf.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Is that true?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes. My father is human, which is why I work for Bayle.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leylia began to catch on. &quot;What did your father do for a
living?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;He is the Temple Knight of Qeynos&quot;<br>
<br>
/That the highest rank of human Paladins, so that must mean his
mother was../<br>
<br>
the Lord Defiler of Neriak.<br>
<br>
&quot;.....under the blood moon two children shall be born..&quot;<br>
<br>
Leylia picks up. &quot;Forged of the purest light and the
blackest dark. And they shall be known as the Dragoon. Masters of<br>
Dragon Kind..<br>
<br>
The dark elf concludes &quot;....Holders of the destiny of
Norrath, the heralds of the Twilight.&quot;<br>
<br>
The dark elf falls to his knees. &quot;I don't believe it. All
this time, I thought...I was told it was a myth..A tale from old
maids....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Now you know it's true. Join us?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's seems fate has lead us together for a reason. I guess
we can go to Qeynos. I was done here anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So that means you know the way?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes of course.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Great!...say we don't even know you're name.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Tenrou....Tenrou Ug'ets&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice to meet you Tenrou.&quot; Leylia helped Tenrou up to
his feet.<br>
<br>
&quot;And just because we are friends now, doesn't mean that
you're going to get out of paying for ruining my favorite shirt!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't do it!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So.&quot; She sticks her tongue out him<br>
<br>
&quot;...Just met you and already in debt.. At least I will be
able to get back to Qeynos and take a bath. Those Dark elf<br>
guildmasters have little concern for our hygiene&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;.....Well. I wasn't going to say anything...&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
Preview of Next Chapter (Spoiler Alert!)<br>
-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Continuing on their journey to Odus with their new ally Tenrou.
The group makes a stop in Highpass hold. The<br>
gateway through the mountain range to Qeynos, the human citadel.
On their way they are branded criminals and bounties<br>
are placed on their heads. Can they make it through to Qeynos, or
does the legend of the Twilight end here? Find out in<br>
the next exciting chapter Rumble at Highpass!<br>
